      "body" : "@jonasschnelli, I don't think it's possible to invalidate a singleShot. There's never any timer exposed for me to invalidate. It functions like the static QMessageBox::info/warning/etc functions.\r\n\r\nI would expect that Qt planned for the possibility of the connected object disappearing, seeing as it could happen often. A quick google turns up that signals are automatically disconnected: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/10570857/are-signals-in-qt-automatically-disconnected-when-one-of-the-class-is-deleted",
      "commit_id" : "f42b2f9e2791196fa01ec55df2d6194bee1fb0a0",
      "created_at" : "2016-05-06T08:59:05Z",
